    {
      "id": "5cjHf10PbQgvRDf5uomdY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 11815.871019102053,
      "y": 9298.889008463017,
      "width": 1919.8082275390625,
      "height": 45,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6p",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1550855593,
      "version": 111,
      "versionNonce": 1740370729,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776096387559,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Ran Diebold Mariano between these two models. 9 feature model is significantly better, but feature analysis ",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Ran Diebold Mariano between these two models. 9 feature model is significantly better, but feature analysis ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "V0HSJZi9DQC5bsTnKeYq8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 7810.853886336222,
      "y": 7065.140750473101,
      "width": 2451.7815907995996,
      "height": 1417.0703124999989,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b6q",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 130245159,
      "version": 402,
      "versionNonce": 298146281,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776105323514,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The DM test found the 9-feature model to be statistically\nsignificantly better than the 6-feature model (p < 0.05), with\nvalidation NSE of 0.836 vs 0.810 and test NSE of 0.811 vs 0.730.\nHowever, the 9-feature model's Shapley analysis revealed severe\nmulticollinearity  (individual feature importances ranged from -\n146.8% to +206.9%) meaning the model's internal attributions are\nphysically uninterpretable, even though its predictions are more\naccurate.\n\nThe 6-feature model, while statistically inferior in, produced\nstable and physically coherent feature attributions (Precip 48.3%,\nPrecip 30d 48.0%), confirming that the feature reduction\nsuccessfully resolved the multicollinearity at the cost of removing\nshort-term precipitation signals the model was leveraging for peak\nflow prediction.",
      "fontSize": 75.57708333333329,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The DM test found the 9-feature model to be statistically significantly better than the 6-feature model (p < 0.05), with validation NSE of 0.836 vs 0.810 and test NSE of 0.811 vs 0.730. However, the 9-feature model's Shapley analysis revealed severe multicollinearity  (individual feature importances ranged from -146.8% to +206.9%) meaning the model's internal attributions are physically uninterpretable, even though its predictions are more accurate.\n\nThe 6-feature model, while statistically inferior in, produced stable and physically coherent feature attributions (Precip 48.3%, Precip 30d 48.0%), confirming that the feature reduction successfully resolved the multicollinearity at the cost of removing short-term precipitation signals the model was leveraging for peak flow prediction.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
